								<title xml:lang="en">Numbers</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="162r" to="191r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Deuteronomy</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">191 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>270</height>
										<width>190</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>195</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>191 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning with watermark and at the end. Folio 192 is blank and unfoliated).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>19 quires: i-xvi10 (folios 1-160), xvii12 (folios 161-172), xviii10 (folios 173-182), xix12 (folios 183-192). </p>
									<p>No catchwords.</p>
									<p>Quire numbers are in the lower left corner of the first folios. </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="41">
									<p>Ruling is visible. </p>
									<p>Flesh and hair sides are clearly distinguishable.
</p>
									<p>Watermark [coat of arms with fleur-de-lis, beneath: LVG] is similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">1852</ref> .</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian-Ashkenazi semi-cursive script, unpunctuated. The letter 'alef' is in a Sefardi style throughout. <name type="person" role="scribe">Arieh Ḥalfan ben Eli῾ezer Ḥalfan</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, together with <name type="person" role="patron">Pinḥas Yaḳar ben Yitsḥaḳ Yaḳar</name>: dated <date calendar="Hebrew">Tamuz 5251</date>, folio 191r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A former owner's note, folio 1v: שלי [... ].  קניתיו אלינקנטו בדמים יקרים ה' יזכני להגות בו אני וזרעי וזרע זרעי עם שאר ספרי הקדש ברוב טוב וחיים טובים וברכה ושלו' מעתה ועד עולם. Owner's name has been cut out after the word שלי. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Pre-1600. Brown leather with clasps and metalic corners, tooled in gold.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'R. Mosis ben Nachman Commentarius in Pentateuchum. Hebraice. Mus. Brit. Jure. Empt. 18,731.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
